# Project Architecture and Context

Monorepo for VkSplat-based 3D Gaussian Splatting training research.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `ref/` | Frozen reference VkSplat, read-only ground truth at `ref-baseline-2026-06-12` |
| `ref/vksplat/` | Reference CMake/Python project root |
| `next/nlrc_vksplat/` | Clean-slate cross-platform rewrite; all new implementation work goes here |
| `test_data/` | Shared regression fixtures and golden masters |
| `outputs/` | Training runs and buffer dumps; gitignored |

## Rewrite Verification

- Catch2/CTest executable: `nlrc_vksplat_tests`.
- Headless Vulkan substrate: `nlrc_vksplat_gpu`.
- Fixture-first isolated GPU tests use invariant and ref-parity oracles.
- Buffer/binding parity follows `rewrite-buffer-contract.mdc`.
- Port order follows `rewrite-porting-order.mdc`.
- Error policy follows `rewrite-error-handling.mdc`.

## Targets

- Windows x86_64: MSVC or Clang via Ninja using `windows-debug` / `windows-release`.
- OpenHarmony ARM64: OHOS NDK via Clang using `ohos-debug` / `ohos-release`.
- Presets live in `next/nlrc_vksplat/CMakePresets.json`.

## Compute Stack

- Vulkan 1.2 baseline.
- Slang for core compute pipelines.
- GLSL 460 for radix sort only.
- Embedded SPIR-V headers generated at CMake build time.

## Current Rewrite Shape

Current low-level rewrite abstractions are `HeadlessContext`, `StorageBuffer`, `ComputePipeline`, typed spans/views, and fixture/golden test helpers.

Ref lineage is `VulkanGSPipeline -> VulkanGSRenderer -> VulkanGSTrainer`; treat that as reference context only, not current rewrite structure.

## Config Propagation

- Rewrite config source of truth: `next/nlrc_vksplat/src/nlrc_vksplat_config.hpp`.
- CMake profile options select only emulation profile flags.
- `scripts/compile_shaders.py` emits generated config fragments and embedded SPIR-V headers under `${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/generated/`.
- Ref config uses `vksplat_config.h` plus runtime `.spv` loading; do not copy that runtime loading model into the rewrite.

## Authoritative Docs

- `README.md`: repo overview and build entrypoints.
- `ref/docs/shader-pipeline.md`: GPU stages, buffer I/O, and subgraphs A-G.
- `ref/docs/ohos-maleoon910-porting-report.md`: OpenHarmony / Maleoon 910 constraints.
- `next/nlrc_vksplat/docs/testing-report.md`: current test coverage, known gaps, and hardening backlog.
